00:55:51.414 --> 00:55:55.294
You want it to be absolutely intact in the serum and in the periphery, but rapidly

960
00:55:55.394 --> 00:55:57.234
activate in the tumor microenvironment.

961
00:55:57.814 --> 00:56:01.774
And in order to screen our library, what we did is we took a MASP molecule in

962
00:56:01.834 --> 00:56:05.314
schematic here, and we differed just that cleavable linker, which is

963
00:56:05.374 --> 00:56:06.714
that dotted line there.

964
00:56:07.534 --> 00:56:09.904
We took these molecules and we fluorescently labeled them.

965
00:56:09.974 --> 00:56:13.954
And to screen for stability, we took serum from either healthy

966
00:56:14.014 --> 00:56:17.934
donors or donors with cancer. And we, over time, look for loss

967
00:56:17.954 --> 00:56:18.594
of the mask.

968
00:56:19.494 --> 00:56:22.854
And what we found is that for both healthy serum and for serum from cancer

969
00:56:22.934 --> 00:56:26.563
patients, the clinical benchmarks show significant activation, that is

970
00:56:26.634 --> 00:56:28.534
cleavage of that linker over time.

971
00:56:28.974 --> 00:56:31.834
And this is a compartment that you don't want active molecule.

972
00:56:31.874 --> 00:56:34.054
And here we have sort of a slow

973
00:56:35.014 --> 00:56:36.984
leak of these active molecules in circulation.

974
00:56:37.914 --> 00:56:41.614
Compare that to the VORA molecules, which are indistinguishable from non-cleavable

975
00:56:41.654 --> 00:56:45.404
control. And across healthy tissue and four different indications, we've

976
00:56:45.474 --> 00:56:47.974
demonstrated superiority over the clinical benchmarks.

977
00:56:50.214 --> 00:56:54.174
Switching now to activation, we ran a similar assay where we took fresh tumor

978
00:56:54.214 --> 00:56:57.854
tissue from patients. We minimally process it in order to keep the tumor

979
00:56:57.874 --> 00:57:01.854
microenvironment intact. And again, we look for loss of the mask in

980
00:57:01.874 --> 00:57:05.744
our labeled molecules. And what we found is that across seven different indications

981
00:57:05.774 --> 00:57:09.754
and 35 different tissue samples, the clinical benchmark linkers have about a

982
00:57:09.814 --> 00:57:12.514
10 to 12-fold activation over 24 hours.

983
00:57:13.174 --> 00:57:17.164
Compare that to our best VORA linkers that show at least threefold increased

984
00:57:17.214 --> 00:57:19.954
activity over that, across all indications.

985
00:57:22.234 --> 00:57:26.154
This combination of improved tumor microenvironment activation and enhanced

986
00:57:26.174 --> 00:57:30.074
serum stability allows us to achieve between 500 and almost 1,000-fold

987
00:57:30.394 --> 00:57:34.294
tumor selectivity. Compare that to the clinical benchmarks that achieve

988
00:57:34.394 --> 00:57:35.794
only five to 14-fold.

989
00:57:38.494 --> 00:57:42.214
Now we've applied these masks and linker technology to a variety of programs,

990
00:57:42.314 --> 00:57:46.094
including an immunocytokine, an early-stage T-cell engager, and

991
00:57:46.104 --> 00:57:50.044
antibody-drug conjugate. But all of the data that I've shown so far, and all the

992
00:57:50.114 --> 00:57:54.094
data that I'll focus on next, has been with our lead molecule, VORA101, which is

993
00:57:54.154 --> 00:57:56.053
a high-affinity CD47 binder.

994
00:57:57.814 --> 00:58:00.474
Now, CD47 is a clinically validated target.

995
00:58:00.694 --> 00:58:04.414
It is a ubiquitously expressed "don't eat me" signal, which is on the

996
00:58:04.454 --> 00:58:05.914
surface of every cell of your body.

997
00:58:06.594 --> 00:58:10.424
And this ubiquitous expression leads to somewhat of a double-edged sword for

998
00:58:10.554 --> 00:58:10.954
targeting.

999
00:58:11.794 --> 00:58:15.574
On-target binding in the tumor with an active Fc leads to potent tumor cell

1000
00:58:15.634 --> 00:58:18.094
killing mediated by macrophages and ADCP.

1001
00:58:18.934 --> 00:58:22.334
However, off-tumor binding leads to dose-limiting toxicities,

1002
00:58:23.314 --> 00:58:27.154
mostly through anemia and thrombocytopenia, and suffers from a massive tissue sink.

1003
00:58:28.194 --> 00:58:32.074
It's this off-tumor binding that has been the Achilles heel for all legacy

1004
00:58:32.114 --> 00:58:35.554
CD47 programs and is directly addressed by the PrimeBody

1005
00:58:35.634 --> 00:58:38.314
platform, wherein we have no binding in

1006
00:58:39.574 --> 00:58:43.034
off-tumor, but maintain on-target binding and tumor efficacy.

1007
00:58:46.874 --> 00:58:50.734
In the absence of masking, all legacy CD47 programs have had to

1008
00:58:50.774 --> 00:58:53.894
take compromises in their on-target tumor efficacy in order to

1009
00:58:53.934 --> 00:58:56.934
address this off-tumor binding toxicity concern.

1010
00:58:58.294 --> 00:59:02.054
An example of this, and a rare success for the CD47 field, is

1011
00:59:02.074 --> 00:59:04.974
avoracept. Avoracept is a high-affinity

1012
00:59:05.674 --> 00:59:09.354
SIRPalpha, which is the ligand for CD47, fused with a null

1013
00:59:09.474 --> 00:59:12.364
Fc. And it's that null Fc that's the compromise.

1014
00:59:12.994 --> 00:59:16.594
As a single agent, it is safe to administer, but it has no single agent

1015
00:59:16.654 --> 00:59:20.554
activity and has to be co-administered with a regimen that includes an active

1016
00:59:20.634 --> 00:59:24.474
Fc. In this case, it's trastuzumab in a HER2-positive

1017
00:59:24.554 --> 00:59:25.914
gastric cancer population.

1018
00:59:26.974 --> 00:59:30.074
Now, in a Phase II trial, the combination of avoracept plus

1019
00:59:30.214 --> 00:59:34.094
TRP in the intent to treat population showed an improvement in

1020
00:59:34.154 --> 00:59:37.694
ORR and medium duration of response over TRP alone.

1021
00:59:38.174 --> 00:59:42.034
And this difference was further amplified in a subset analysis, where about

1022
00:59:42.194 --> 00:59:45.934
40% of the improved ORR is attributable to CD47,

1023
00:59:46.394 --> 00:59:48.694
highlighting the power of targeting CD47.

1024
00:59:49.254 --> 00:59:52.804
However, this is only in the context of an active Fc provided by

1025
00:59:52.894 --> 00:59:55.154
trastuzumab in a HER2-positive population.

1026
00:59:56.974 --> 01:00:00.914
To put this into context, if we look at the CD47 landscape, we can see

1027
01:00:00.934 --> 01:00:04.574
it's very crowded. But if we plot these based off of either their Fc

1028
01:00:04.634 --> 01:00:08.534
activity on the x-axis or their CD47 affinity, we

1029
01:00:08.594 --> 01:00:10.414
find that there's a pattern that emerges.

1030
01:00:10.444 --> 01:00:14.334
And that is that they have all had to take either compromises in their Fc

1031
01:00:14.374 --> 01:00:18.194
activity using null or weak formats, or in their

1032
01:00:18.214 --> 01:00:22.174
CD47 affinity. And it is only when you take a high-affinity

1033
01:00:22.234 --> 01:00:25.614
CD47 binder like avoracept and add it to

1034
01:00:25.714 --> 01:00:29.344
an active Fc, in this case trastuzumab, that you get

1035
01:00:29.374 --> 01:00:33.234
potent patient responses. This requirement for

1036
01:00:33.274 --> 01:00:36.754
both CD47 blockade and Fc activity was also shown

1037
01:00:36.774 --> 01:00:40.614
preclinically by the Ravetch lab and our esteemed chairperson, Juan Soriano, in a

1038
01:00:40.654 --> 01:00:44.634
triple humanized mouse model where they utilized a CD47 antibody

1039
01:00:44.674 --> 01:00:48.394
with an enhanced Fc and demonstrated curative activity with

1040
01:00:48.404 --> 01:00:52.054
systemic antitumor activity. However, this was limited to

1041
01:00:52.094 --> 01:00:55.494
intratumoral injection, and the systemic dose was too toxic.

1042
01:00:56.954 --> 01:01:00.614
Because with masking, we are addressing both the tissue sink and the

1043
01:01:00.654 --> 01:01:04.534
toxicity concerns, we are able to, for the first time, use

1044
01:01:04.614 --> 01:01:08.274
a high-affinity CD47 binder and an enhanced Fc.

1045
01:01:09.094 --> 01:01:12.834
And this really produces the first no compromises CD47

1046
01:01:12.874 --> 01:01:15.874
therapeutic and represents a new mechanism of action.

1047
01:01:16.454 --> 01:01:20.054
In a single molecule, by targeting CD47, we are not only

1048
01:01:20.074 --> 01:01:23.894
blocking the "don't eat me" checkpoint blockade from CD47, but also

1049
01:01:23.934 --> 01:01:27.494
using it as a tumor antigen itself for ADCC and ADCP.

1050
01:01:28.263 --> 01:01:31.994
And what we found is that in an in vitro phagocytosis model, we got very

1051
01:01:32.054 --> 01:01:35.834
potent activity with our non-MASP molecule shown in pink, well in

1052
01:01:35.854 --> 01:01:39.374
excess in both magnitude and potency of the clinical controls.

1053
01:01:41.494 --> 01:01:45.354
Even with this extreme potency, when we optimize for both MASP and linker,

1054
01:01:45.874 --> 01:01:49.766
we are able to push that potency 2,000-fold to the right.Importantly,

1055
01:01:49.836 --> 01:01:53.686
this is now below the level of ALX-148, which is avariccept,

